WEBVTT

00:02.078 --> 00:03.344
All right, Chuck, we're gonna

00:03.346 --> 00:04.979
walk you through the commercial here.

00:04.981 --> 00:06.414
Now, as you know,

00:06.416 --> 00:08.148
the camera is gonna be the point of view

00:08.151 --> 00:10.084
of the little Husky Boy shopper,

00:10.086 --> 00:11.630
so we open on:

00:11.655 --> 00:13.667
he enters the store.

00:13.713 --> 00:16.306
The camera pans up. He looks to Mom.

00:16.332 --> 00:17.815
It comes back down.

00:17.817 --> 00:19.983
We see a bunch of fat
little boys in suits.

00:19.985 --> 00:21.585
- Husky boys.
- I'm sorry?

00:21.587 --> 00:23.320
We don't call 'em
fat. We call 'em husky.

00:23.322 --> 00:26.023
Oh. Okay, sure.

00:26.025 --> 00:27.391
Then we see some tennis outfits

00:27.393 --> 00:29.368
being worn by a couple real chunkers.

00:29.393 --> 00:30.696
- Husky boys.
- I'm sorry?

00:30.721 --> 00:32.087
Again, we call 'em husky boys.

00:32.110 --> 00:33.810
Oh, you're not just objecting to "fat."

00:33.813 --> 00:35.079
You don't like any of the terms.

00:35.080 --> 00:37.013
Oh, we just prefer to use "husky."

00:37.015 --> 00:38.448
Got it. Okay.

00:38.451 --> 00:39.750
To bring it all home,

00:39.752 --> 00:41.886
we feature your soon-to-be-famous

00:41.888 --> 00:43.721
elastic band jeans

00:43.723 --> 00:46.690
being worn by a real
blue-ribbon butterball.

00:46.692 --> 00:48.692
I apologize. That is
what's written down there.

00:48.694 --> 00:50.628
I am sorry about that. Husky boy.

00:51.213 --> 00:52.730
Being worn by a husky boy.

00:52.732 --> 00:55.566
- It's not as good.
- No, it definitely isn't.

00:55.567 --> 00:57.867
Then in our dramatic conclusion,

00:57.870 --> 00:59.536
we see two chubby little hands...

00:59.538 --> 01:01.438
- Husky.
- Even the hands?

01:01.440 --> 01:03.173
- Everything.
- All right.

01:03.175 --> 01:06.911
- Uh, we see two husky hands...
- Ugh!

01:06.913 --> 01:09.580
- Not covered in chocolate.
- That kills me.

01:09.581 --> 01:12.282
They reach down, pick up
a pair of Husky Boy jeans.

01:12.284 --> 01:13.616
Stretch this out a little bit.

01:13.618 --> 01:14.751
Yeah, stretch it out a little bit.

01:14.754 --> 01:16.287
He looks up. Mom smiles.

01:16.289 --> 01:18.255
He's gonna look great.

01:18.257 --> 01:20.024
End of commercial.

01:20.384 --> 01:22.793
- Nice. Yeah.
- Thank you.

01:22.794 --> 01:25.561
Maybe a tagline at the end,
you know, to bring it all home?

01:25.563 --> 01:27.463
Uh, you know what? We
haven't landed on one yet,

01:27.465 --> 01:29.632
but we'll write up 100
and bring you the best one.

01:29.634 --> 01:31.301
Actually, we do have
a couple great ones.

01:31.303 --> 01:32.635
Uh, no we don't. The meeting's over.

01:32.637 --> 01:33.903
Let's see, uh, "Husky Boys:

01:33.906 --> 01:35.439
keep your wallet as fat as your kid."

01:35.441 --> 01:37.908
- That seems a little offensive.
- Sure does, Sam.

01:37.909 --> 01:39.609
Sorry, we don't have
one yet. I apologize.

01:39.611 --> 01:42.011
"Don't spend a chunk on your chunk."

01:42.013 --> 01:43.012
No.

01:43.014 --> 01:44.948
We don't have it yet.

01:44.950 --> 01:47.150
I'm sure you'll come up with something.

01:47.153 --> 01:48.819
- Oh, definitely.
- You know, I don't know

01:48.821 --> 01:50.120
if I ever told you this,

01:50.122 --> 01:51.822
but I actually worked with your father

01:51.824 --> 01:53.991
when I was at Hudson's Department Store.

01:53.993 --> 01:55.993
I was actually at the meeting when,

01:56.632 --> 01:58.861
you know, he went nuts.

01:58.863 --> 02:00.129
I prefer "bonkers."

02:00.131 --> 02:02.131
Oh. Of course. Bonkers.

02:02.134 --> 02:03.801
- Thank you.
- Yeah, he came in

02:03.803 --> 02:06.070
to pitch an ad for our
back to school sale,

02:06.463 --> 02:10.007
and he had us close our
eyes, and when we opened them,

02:10.008 --> 02:11.342
he had pulled out this briefcase.

02:11.344 --> 02:12.543
Swear to God,

02:12.545 --> 02:15.312
it was filled to the brim with shit.

02:15.911 --> 02:17.480
And he walked around the table

02:17.483 --> 02:20.718
and put a little handful
in front of each of us.

02:20.720 --> 02:22.686
As he made his way up the table,

02:22.688 --> 02:26.190
I realized he only had
the front half of his suit.

02:26.192 --> 02:28.025
He had cut out the rest.

02:28.557 --> 02:30.026
Totally naked in the back.

02:30.767 --> 02:32.295
I found that to be odd.

02:32.762 --> 02:34.865
So there we were, sitting there,

02:34.867 --> 02:36.533
little servings of shit in front of us,

02:36.566 --> 02:39.070
staring at this half-naked man,

02:39.411 --> 02:40.870
and you know what?

02:41.538 --> 02:44.708
We were still waiting for
him to bring it all home.

02:44.710 --> 02:47.444
That's how good he was, man.

02:47.446 --> 02:50.280
[laughs]

02:50.282 --> 02:51.815
Big Hank Cramblin.

02:52.176 --> 02:54.295
They don't make 'em like that anymore.

02:55.100 --> 02:57.014
Thank you for telling
me that story, sir.

02:57.970 --> 02:59.422
"Husky Boy Jeans.

02:59.425 --> 03:01.358
They're not food, but
you'll still love them."

03:01.834 --> 03:04.327
- Closer.
- We don't have it!

03:04.330 --> 03:06.864
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

03:06.865 --> 03:08.531
I mean, I guess I
just don't want to feel

03:08.534 --> 03:10.501
like I'm being censored
in front of a client.

03:10.502 --> 03:12.368
No, no, no, and I don't
want you to feel that way.

03:12.371 --> 03:14.438
I was just feeling a little
off 'cause I kept forgetting

03:14.440 --> 03:16.140
to call the fat kids "husky."

03:16.142 --> 03:18.075
[laughing] That was so funny.

03:18.077 --> 03:19.443
I mean, you always call them fat.

03:19.444 --> 03:20.843
That's what they are.

03:20.846 --> 03:23.247
[laughter]

03:23.866 --> 03:24.948
Where is Sheila?

03:24.950 --> 03:27.551
[gasps] Tim, finally, a mystery.

03:27.552 --> 03:28.551
Yes.

03:28.554 --> 03:30.054
<i>[Sheila laughing]</i>

03:30.056 --> 03:32.556
- Mystery solved.
- Yeah.

03:32.557 --> 03:34.757
Get me a box of those pens I like.

03:34.760 --> 03:36.794
Set me up with a massage at 2:00.

03:36.796 --> 03:38.395
And see if you can get ahold of Emilio.

03:38.397 --> 03:39.696
Have him come over

03:39.698 --> 03:41.031
and measure me for some new suits.

03:41.032 --> 03:43.433
You got it, Big Hank.

03:44.175 --> 03:45.768
Hey, Dad.

03:46.369 --> 03:47.537
Tim, Sam.

03:47.539 --> 03:48.538
They let you out?

03:48.540 --> 03:49.872
Of the nuthouse?

03:50.330 --> 03:52.285
Yeah, got released this morning.

03:53.113 --> 03:55.646
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:55.648 --> 03:57.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:57.781 --> 03:59.022
I'm back.

04:00.038 --> 04:01.721
You ain't shit.

04:03.130 --> 04:04.281
Never said I was.

04:04.531 --> 04:06.011
Well, you've implied it.

04:06.891 --> 04:07.990
<i>♪ Next time ♪</i>

04:07.993 --> 04:09.126
<i>♪ When they ask you ♪</i>

04:09.128 --> 04:11.428
<i>♪ Where you're from ♪</i>

04:11.430 --> 04:13.263
<i>♪ You gon' say Detroit city ♪</i>

04:13.265 --> 04:17.401
<i>♪ When we get back
on our feet, yeah ♪</i>

04:17.403 --> 04:18.935
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

04:18.938 --> 04:21.872
<i>[laughter and chatter]</i>

04:23.000 --> 04:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:30.667 --> 04:32.115
What is going on in there?

04:32.117 --> 04:33.216
Right?

04:33.219 --> 04:34.651
I've never made anybody

04:34.653 --> 04:36.653
laugh like that my entire life.

04:36.655 --> 04:38.322
- Well, me.
- Yeah, you.

04:38.323 --> 04:39.655
So I said, "Fine, Doc,

04:39.658 --> 04:41.024
"but if you think you're getting

04:41.026 --> 04:42.826
those pajamas back,
<i>you're</i> crazy."

04:42.828 --> 04:44.628
[laughter]

04:44.629 --> 04:46.429
It is great to have you back, Hank.

04:46.431 --> 04:47.530
Thank you.

04:47.532 --> 04:49.265
We missed Cramblin Advertising.

04:49.267 --> 04:51.501
We didn't go anywhere, and
it's Cramblin-Duvet now.

04:51.503 --> 04:53.055
That's me, so...

04:53.538 --> 04:54.871
Tim, you remember Leslie

04:54.874 --> 04:56.607
from Better Made Potato Chips?

04:56.608 --> 04:59.675
Yes, Sam and I pitched you
an idea about a boat captain

04:59.678 --> 05:03.814
piloting a battleship down
a river made of potato chips.

05:04.374 --> 05:06.949
You said you'd think about
it and get back to us.

05:07.594 --> 05:08.967
That was three years ago.

05:09.032 --> 05:10.320
Oh, yeah.

05:10.954 --> 05:12.303
Sorry about that.

05:15.225 --> 05:16.193
The answer is no.

05:16.195 --> 05:17.461
- Sure.
- We figured.

05:17.462 --> 05:19.829
It's just good to know sometimes.

05:19.831 --> 05:21.864
Well, it's great to
have you back, Big Hank.

05:21.866 --> 05:24.300
Thank you, Leslie. Thank you so much.

05:25.008 --> 05:28.548
Guys, you ready to wine and
dine Dan from Downriver Ale?

05:28.670 --> 05:29.897
Top of the Pontch.

05:30.708 --> 05:33.255
Oh, Dad, Sam and I should stay here.

05:33.579 --> 05:35.211
Tim, Top of the Pontch.

05:35.213 --> 05:37.914
We have to come up with
taglines for Husky Boys.

05:37.916 --> 05:39.682
Small potatoes.

05:39.685 --> 05:42.286
Let's go reel us in a
big fish from Downriver.

05:43.322 --> 05:46.356
<i>[funky music]</i>

05:46.358 --> 05:53.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:21.077 --> 06:22.717
<i>[laughter]</i>

06:22.788 --> 06:23.953
So I drop the knife.

06:23.955 --> 06:25.989
My hands are covered in blood.

06:25.991 --> 06:27.524
And here comes Hank

06:27.526 --> 06:31.261
riding a motorcycle he
stole from God knows where.

06:31.263 --> 06:33.163
I hop on, shut my eyes,

06:33.165 --> 06:35.999
and the next thing I know,
we're back in San Diego!

06:36.001 --> 06:37.100
[laughter]

06:37.102 --> 06:38.702
I don't get it.

06:38.727 --> 06:41.997
Did Dan from Downriver
Ale kill a guy in Mexico?

06:42.022 --> 06:43.707
I mean, I think so?

06:43.709 --> 06:45.175
Four Downriver Ales.

06:45.177 --> 06:46.242
Yeah, what are you guys having?

06:46.244 --> 06:47.610
[laughter]

06:47.612 --> 06:49.779
I-I thought one of those was for me.

06:49.781 --> 06:52.248
Yeah, I guess we'll
have four beers each too.

06:52.250 --> 06:54.017
Give us four hanger steaks, rare,

06:54.019 --> 06:55.785
all the sides the table can hold,

06:55.787 --> 06:57.220
and, well, another round.

06:57.222 --> 06:58.855
I wanted the filet.

06:58.857 --> 07:01.044
To our wives and girlfriends.

07:01.460 --> 07:02.792
May they never meet!

07:02.794 --> 07:04.961
[laughter]

07:04.963 --> 07:07.764
Oh! Hey, Dan, let's talk turkey.

07:07.766 --> 07:09.132
You know, I have to say something.

07:09.134 --> 07:10.400
I didn't particularly like that joke.

07:10.402 --> 07:11.801
I love my wife.

07:11.803 --> 07:14.270
- Well, sure, kid. I was just...
- I respect her.

07:14.272 --> 07:16.239
And before I tell a joke,
I like to ask myself,

07:16.241 --> 07:18.767
"If she was sitting right next
to me, would I tell this joke?"

07:19.311 --> 07:21.678
That comment crossed the line.
I don't think it was very funny.

07:23.281 --> 07:24.347
[clears throat]

07:25.984 --> 07:28.318
It's great to see you
again, Hank, but...

07:28.320 --> 07:30.653
everybody at Downriver
Ale is happy where we are.

07:30.655 --> 07:33.757
Our ads are hilarious.

07:33.759 --> 07:35.492
People love 'em.

07:35.494 --> 07:37.284
Yeah, they are funny.

07:37.963 --> 07:40.563
Tim, Sam, what's your favorite beer?

07:40.565 --> 07:42.999
- Downriver Ale.
- Why is that?

07:43.001 --> 07:44.408
Because you drank it.

07:44.836 --> 07:46.469
I used to steal his
beers from the fridge

07:46.471 --> 07:48.371
in the garage while he was at work.

07:48.373 --> 07:51.141
I always wondered how my
six-packs became four-packs.

07:51.143 --> 07:52.575
[laughter]

07:52.577 --> 07:55.278
You know, Dan, your
commercials are funny.

07:55.280 --> 07:57.247
But there's nothing funny
about the feeling you get

07:57.249 --> 07:59.182
when you steal a beer
out of your dad's fridge.

07:59.184 --> 08:00.750
Do you want to be the funny beer?

08:00.752 --> 08:02.218
You go ahead.

08:02.220 --> 08:05.555
With us, Downriver Ale, it's no joke.

08:09.594 --> 08:11.427
To our mouths and buttholes.

08:11.429 --> 08:13.296
May they never meet.

08:13.298 --> 08:14.544
- Yes.
- Hear, hear.

08:14.569 --> 08:15.999
[laughter]

08:16.001 --> 08:17.801
Now, that's a good joke.

08:18.870 --> 08:21.037
<i>[smooth R&B music]</i>

08:21.460 --> 08:23.506
Sheila, pot of coffee, two aspirin.

08:23.508 --> 08:25.642
Waiting on your desk, Big Hank.

08:25.644 --> 08:27.110
Best in the business, baby!

08:27.112 --> 08:28.878
I can't believe how much they drank.

08:28.880 --> 08:30.146
What about me?

08:30.148 --> 08:32.048
I had two pieces of chocolate cake.

08:32.049 --> 08:33.716
Yeah, what was that?

08:34.041 --> 08:35.351
Nobody else got dessert.

08:35.352 --> 08:37.220
We had to sit there and
watch you for 20 minutes.

08:37.222 --> 08:38.688
Oh, so that's the top story now?

08:38.690 --> 08:40.289
That I had two pieces of cake for lunch?

08:40.587 --> 08:42.025
It's page one, baby.

08:42.027 --> 08:42.991
Shut up.

08:42.994 --> 08:44.360
"Husky Boys:

08:44.696 --> 08:46.129
"Technically girls

08:46.131 --> 08:47.603
can shop here too."

08:47.899 --> 08:49.065
That's great.

08:49.067 --> 08:50.466
"Husky Boys:

08:50.468 --> 08:52.202
We're gonna hide the way you look."

08:52.204 --> 08:55.505
"Husky Boys: the official
wardrobe of the Klumps."

08:55.507 --> 08:57.373
"Husky Boys: 'Cause you can't wear

08:57.375 --> 08:59.242
a little sailor suit forever."

08:59.244 --> 09:02.045
"Husky Boys: the belts
are just for show."

09:02.047 --> 09:03.336
"Husky Boys:

09:04.148 --> 09:05.715
Chode style."

09:05.717 --> 09:09.352
"Husky Boys: Propeller
hat not included."

09:09.816 --> 09:11.688
And that's 100.

09:11.690 --> 09:13.890
Well, which one's the best one?

09:14.285 --> 09:16.392
- None of them.
- Well, we tried.

09:16.394 --> 09:18.494
I'm gonna go run some
of these by my dad.

09:19.898 --> 09:21.130
[knocking]

09:22.868 --> 09:23.900
Hey, Dad.

09:23.902 --> 09:25.568
Uh, you mind if we run

09:25.570 --> 09:28.171
some of these Husky Boy taglines by you?

09:28.173 --> 09:29.606
Oh, can't, son.

09:29.608 --> 09:31.207
Got Liberty Airlines
first thing tomorrow.

09:31.209 --> 09:32.274
Lot of catching up to do.

09:32.693 --> 09:33.842
Okay, cool.

09:34.203 --> 09:35.879
Uh, do you need any help with those?

09:36.948 --> 09:38.052
[chuckles softly]

09:38.416 --> 09:39.789
I think I got it.

09:40.085 --> 09:42.552
Maybe I'll meet up with
you guys later on tonight.

09:42.953 --> 09:43.853
Sounds good.

09:43.855 --> 09:46.890
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

09:46.892 --> 09:52.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:52.764 --> 09:54.197
[rock music playing]

09:54.199 --> 09:59.135
<i>♪ 313-555-0197 ♪</i>

09:59.137 --> 10:00.670
<i>Frank Franklin.</i>

10:00.694 --> 10:02.473
_

10:02.474 --> 10:03.640
That was one of the first commercials

10:03.642 --> 10:05.208
we ever did together.

10:05.210 --> 10:06.943
Yeah, we heard that melody
in another commercial

10:06.945 --> 10:08.710
and we were like, "Let's just use that."

10:09.614 --> 10:11.381
I'm gonna miss being in charge.

10:11.383 --> 10:12.803
Yeah, it was a good run, though, pal.

10:12.828 --> 10:13.826
Oh, sure was.

10:13.826 --> 10:15.693
<i>Guards at the Wayne
County Insane Asylum</i>

10:15.695 --> 10:18.162
<i>went on strike this morning
after their paychecks bounced.</i>

10:18.164 --> 10:19.764
<i>When pressed for comment,</i>

10:19.766 --> 10:22.633
<i>lawmakers said it was not
a mistake, saying, quote</i>

10:22.635 --> 10:25.708
<i>"We were just hoping
they wouldn't notice."</i>

10:26.403 --> 10:28.639
<i>And while the cats were
away, the mice escaped,</i>

10:28.641 --> 10:31.275
<i>as shown in this
security footage.</i>

10:34.588 --> 10:36.546
- Damn it, he's still nuts!
- Bonkers.

10:36.549 --> 10:38.182
<i>Tonight, dangerous lunatics</i>

10:38.184 --> 10:41.185
<i>are scattered around
the city of Detroit.</i>

10:41.187 --> 10:44.055
<i>[laughing] But what
else is new, right?</i>

10:44.057 --> 10:45.856
<i>We'll be right back
with sports, weather,</i>

10:45.858 --> 10:47.558
<i>and my Chump of the Week.</i>

10:47.560 --> 10:48.859
<i>Stick with us.</i>

10:49.369 --> 10:51.436
All right, let's go get 'em.

10:51.461 --> 10:53.781
Well, Tim, we can't miss
Mort Crim's Chump of the Week.

10:53.973 --> 10:55.979
- Come on, Sam.
- Tim, Chump of the Week.

10:56.004 --> 10:58.469
- Come on!
- Ugh!

11:00.335 --> 11:01.724
Stupid.

11:05.245 --> 11:06.811
[elevator dings]

11:11.414 --> 11:13.017
There's a gigantic man in your office.

11:13.019 --> 11:14.752
He gave me some great
notes on a commercial,

11:14.754 --> 11:18.168
and then he asked me to cut
out the back half of his suit.

11:18.309 --> 11:20.633
Yeah, we're on it. That's my dad.

11:20.658 --> 11:22.191
That's your dad?

11:22.193 --> 11:23.525
Yeah.

11:23.526 --> 11:25.112
You did not come from that.

11:25.137 --> 11:26.695
Yes, I did. It's my dad.

11:27.797 --> 11:28.863
Good night, guys.

11:28.865 --> 11:31.833
Good night. [scoffs]

11:31.835 --> 11:34.903
<i>And that sucker is Mort
Crim's Chump of the Week.</i>

11:34.905 --> 11:36.571
<i>Good night, Detroit.</i>

11:36.573 --> 11:38.072
Damn it, Tim.

11:38.074 --> 11:39.774
- We missed the Chump of the Week. <i>
- [line ringing]</i>

11:39.776 --> 11:41.409
And you know Mort
doesn't put stuff online.

11:41.411 --> 11:42.744
I'm sorry.

11:42.746 --> 11:44.312
[phone rings]

11:44.314 --> 11:46.581
Wayne County Insane Asylum.

11:46.583 --> 11:49.217
Hi, this is Tim Cramblin from
Cramblin-Duvet Advertising.

11:49.219 --> 11:51.019
We have one of your lunatics.

11:51.021 --> 11:54.255
- It's my dad, Hank Cramblin. <i>
- Oh, okay.</i>

11:54.257 --> 11:56.057
I need to put you in
contact with the orderlies

11:56.059 --> 11:57.725
who are rounding up the patients.

11:57.727 --> 11:59.327
They're putting me in
touch with the orderlies

11:59.329 --> 12:00.762
who are rounding up all the patients.

12:00.764 --> 12:01.763
Oh, cool.

12:01.765 --> 12:04.499
[beatboxing]

12:04.501 --> 12:06.968
♪ We out here driving
late at night ♪

12:06.970 --> 12:09.270
♪ Looking for crazy
people, what a fright ♪

12:09.272 --> 12:10.838
♪ You look to the left ♪

12:10.840 --> 12:12.473
- ♪ Look to the right ♪
- [cell phone buzzes]

12:12.475 --> 12:14.242
- Hello? <i>
- Hello, boys.</i>

12:14.244 --> 12:16.577
I have the son of one
of the escaped patients.

12:16.579 --> 12:18.579
Thanks, Helen. Put him through.

12:18.581 --> 12:20.048
This is Darron. How may I help you?

12:20.050 --> 12:21.015
Uh, yeah, hi.

12:21.017 --> 12:22.283
Uh, we have my dad,

12:22.285 --> 12:23.651
who escaped from your asylum.

12:23.653 --> 12:24.919
Is anyone in danger?

12:24.921 --> 12:26.321
No, he seems fine.

12:26.323 --> 12:28.856
Okay, if you can,
bring him in yourselves.

12:28.858 --> 12:31.526
We got a lot of nutballs to scoop up.

12:32.092 --> 12:33.028
No offense to your father.

12:33.029 --> 12:34.595
<i>Oh, none taken.</i>

12:34.597 --> 12:35.997
We'll bring him in, okay?

12:35.999 --> 12:37.398
Okay. Thank you, sir.

12:37.400 --> 12:38.800
Thank you.

12:38.802 --> 12:40.201
There go one of 'em right there!

12:40.203 --> 12:41.202
Get him.

12:41.204 --> 12:43.137
[tires squealing, all groan]

12:45.331 --> 12:46.885
<i>[holiday music playing on TV]</i>

12:46.910 --> 12:48.328
Hey, Pop.

12:48.735 --> 12:50.410
Good evening, Mr. Cramblin.

12:51.004 --> 12:52.837
I was going through some stuff,

12:52.839 --> 12:55.172
found this video of
an old Christmas party.

12:55.174 --> 12:58.876
<i>[applause]</i>

12:58.878 --> 13:01.138
<i>Whoa, what's Santa
got old Wallace here?</i>

13:01.806 --> 13:04.024
<i>What? It's an empty
bottle of gin, Wallace.</i>

13:04.646 --> 13:06.690
Both: Oh, Wallace.

13:07.148 --> 13:08.314
<i>We found so many in your desk,</i>

13:08.316 --> 13:09.615
<i>we figured you collected them.</i>

13:09.617 --> 13:11.584
<i>[laughter]</i>

13:11.586 --> 13:13.152
[chuckles]

13:13.527 --> 13:15.721
<i>What'd you get me, Santa Hank?</i>

13:15.723 --> 13:17.156
Whoa, look at Sheila.

13:17.158 --> 13:20.133
Yeah, she was even hotter back then.

13:20.662 --> 13:21.894
<i>Ho, ho, ho!</i>

13:21.896 --> 13:24.013
<i>Well, if Big Hank was here,</i>

13:24.499 --> 13:26.532
<i>I'm sure he'd tell you
all thank you so much</i>

13:26.534 --> 13:28.447
<i>for another amazing year,</i>

13:28.990 --> 13:30.136
<i>and merry Christmas.</i>

13:30.138 --> 13:31.804
<i>All: Merry Christmas.</i>

13:31.806 --> 13:34.073
<i>Ho! Look, my little elves!</i>

13:34.075 --> 13:35.942
<i>And they got a cake!</i>

13:35.944 --> 13:37.243
<i>[applause]</i>

13:37.245 --> 13:39.912
[Both chuckling]

13:39.914 --> 13:41.414
<i>All: Oh!</i>

13:41.416 --> 13:43.115
<i>Crap! Damn it, Sam.</i>

13:43.117 --> 13:45.618
<i>Me? That was your fault, Tim.</i>

13:47.188 --> 13:48.221
[chuckles]

13:48.223 --> 13:50.120
<i>Tim, Sam. Listen up. Stop.</i>

13:50.758 --> 13:52.158
[Both laughing]

13:52.160 --> 13:53.893
<i>All right, guys. Listen up.</i>

13:53.895 --> 13:55.895
<i>Stop it. Dude, stop it.</i>

13:55.897 --> 13:58.030
<i>You actually hurt my back.</i>

13:58.032 --> 13:59.999
<i>You're a tip-to-tail piece of crap.</i>

14:00.001 --> 14:01.901
<i>Okay, you two. Hug and make up.</i>

14:01.903 --> 14:05.004
<i>- You're my best friend.
- You're my best friend.</i>

14:05.006 --> 14:06.839
- [laughter] <i>
- Merry Christmas, boys.</i>

14:06.841 --> 14:08.173
Ah.

14:15.699 --> 14:17.383
We got to bring you back, Dad.

14:20.611 --> 14:22.588
Mort Crim reported the escape

14:22.590 --> 14:24.953
right before he announced
his Chump of the Week.

14:26.814 --> 14:27.993
Who was Chump of the Week?

14:28.468 --> 14:29.996
We don't know.

14:33.234 --> 14:34.266
Well...

14:35.901 --> 14:37.140
I guess this is it.

14:43.593 --> 14:45.113
Dad, wait.

14:45.887 --> 14:48.020
Is there anything you want
to do before we take you back?

14:48.219 --> 14:50.783
One last night in
Detroit. Sky's the limit.

14:51.101 --> 14:52.751
Well, I would like to get
the hell out of this office

14:52.754 --> 14:54.754
and hang out with my
son and his best friend.

14:55.035 --> 14:56.925
- Sounds good.
- You got it.

14:57.158 --> 14:59.458
How about we go to Lindell
AC and get us a burger?

14:59.460 --> 15:01.694
- Oh, sorry, Dad.
- That closed.

15:01.696 --> 15:03.362
- Chin Tiki?
- Demolished.

15:03.364 --> 15:04.930
- Boblo Island.
- It's condos now.

15:04.932 --> 15:06.565
- House I grew up in?
- It's a hipster bar.

15:06.567 --> 15:08.134
- Michigan Theater.
- It's a parking garage.

15:08.136 --> 15:09.769
- Silverdome.
- Abandoned.

15:09.771 --> 15:11.971
- Old Tiger Stadium.
- Dad, they closed

15:11.973 --> 15:13.806
Tiger Stadium before you went nuts.

15:13.808 --> 15:15.941
Plus, you called it Old Tiger Stadium.

15:16.183 --> 15:19.511
Okay, I'd like to see
the sunrise one last time.

15:20.063 --> 15:21.912
Detroit still has a sun, right?

15:22.459 --> 15:23.471
Yeah.

15:23.651 --> 15:26.308
Well, I guess we've
got some time to kill.

